OL,3,CFormer police officer stole #2.50 from
OL,4,Csuspect's car to pay for tuck shop debt
OL,6,FBody-worn video showed him taking the
OL,7,Floose change that was in the centre
OL,8,Fconsole of the vehicle.
OL,10,FTillcock was served with a notice in
OL,11,FJuly and confirmed the theft to the
OL,12,FInvestigating Officer.
OL,14,FAccording to Thames Valley Police, he
OL,15,Fsaid: "It's alright I know why you are
OL,16,Fhere, I was very silly. I was in debt
OL,17,Ffor #2 to the tuck shop and took #2."
