OL,3,CFormer police officer stole #2.50 from
OL,4,Csuspect's car to pay for tuck shop debt
OL,6,FTillcock then admitted taking money
OL,7,Ffrom the car to the value of #2.50 to
OL,8,Fpay a debt to the tuck shop and to
OL,9,Fpurchase chocolate bars for his
OL,10,Fchildren.
OL,12,FThe former police officer received a
OL,13,Fcaution for theft.
OL,15,FTillcock submitted his resignation on
OL,16,F12th August, which took effect on 9th
OL,17,FSeptember.
OL,19,FThe Chief Constable said conduct fell
OL,20,Ffar below the standards expected.
